cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR 

The paper proposes a novel dense descriptor for estimating correspondences in multi-modal and multi-spectral images. This task is closely related to computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) as it involves developing a new descriptor and using discriminative learning to obtain a sampling pattern. The paper also addresses geometric variations, which falls under the category of computer graphics (cs.GR). Additionally, the use of self-similarity and edge-aware filtering suggests a potential connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper explicitly mentions multi-modal and multi-spectral images, indicating a possible fit with the sub-category of multimedia (cs.MM).
